    <h2 id="breaktrans">BreakTrans</h2>

<p>BreakTrans is a computer program that maps predicted gene fusions to genomic structural rearrangements so as to validate both types of events and provide them mechanism/functional interpretation. It requires input from at least one gene fusion prediction program (such as Tophat-fusion, deFuse and <a href="https://bioinformatics.mdanderson.org/public-software/breakfusion/">BreakFusion</a>) and at least one genomic breakpoint detection program
(such as <a href="http://breakdancer.sourceforge.net/" target="_blank">BreakDancer <i class="fas fa-external-link-square-alt"></i></a> and <a href="http://www.stjuderesearch.org/site/lab/zhang" target="_blank">CREST <i class="fas fa-external-link-square-alt"></i></a>).</p>

<h3 id="download">Download</h3>

<p>The BreakTrans package includes two parts, executable files and annotation data files for each specific cancer. To run it, users need to download the executable files and the annotation database.</p>

<p><u><strong>Executable Package (6.5 Kb)</strong></u></p>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://odin.mdacc.tmc.edu/~kchen3/BreakTrans/release-2013-06-15/BreakTrans-0.0.6.tar.bz2" target="_blank">BreakTrans-0.0.6 <i class="fas fa-download"></i></a></li>
<li><a href="http://odin.mdacc.tmc.edu/~kchen3/BreakTrans/release-2013-02-14/BreakTrans-0.0.6/README" target="_blank">README</a></li>
</ul>

<p><u><strong>Annotation database (184 Mb)</strong></u></p>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://odin.mdacc.tmc.edu/~kchen3/BreakTrans/release-2013-02-14/database.tar.bz2" target="_blank">Annotation Database <i class="fas fa-download"></i></a></li>
</ul>

<p><u><strong>Test data set for breast cancer cell-line SK-BR-3 (673 Kb)</strong></u></p>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://odin.mdacc.tmc.edu/~kchen3/BreakTrans/release-2013-02-14/testdata.tar.bz2" target="_blank">Test Data <i class="fas fa-download"></i></a></li>
</ul>

